<h3>{$logwatch->Lang('help_general')}</h3>

<h4>Overview</h4>
<p>LogWatch monitors PHP error logs and displays them in an organized, easy-to-read format within the CMS Made Simple admin panel. It helps developers quickly identify and resolve issues during development and production.</p>

<h4>Quick Start</h4>
<ol>
  <li>Navigate to <strong>Extensions &gt; LogWatch</strong></li>
  <li>Go to the <strong>Settings</strong> tab and select your log source</li>
  <li>Choose which error types to display (Fatal, Warning, Notice, Deprecated)</li>
  <li>View errors in the <strong>Logs</strong> tab</li>
  <li>Click <strong>View</strong> on any error to see full details including stack traces</li>
</ol>

<h4>System Requirements</h4>
<ul>
  <li>CMS Made Simple 2.2.0 or higher</li>
  <li>PHP 7.4 or higher (PHP 8.x compatible)</li>
  <li>Read access to server error log files</li>
</ul>

<h4>Credits</h4>
<p>This module uses the <a href="https://github.com/kassner/log-parser" target="_blank">kassner/log-parser</a> library for robust Apache log parsing.</p>
